<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="782" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760p.61/114: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-14T10:00:00+02:00">October
                                    14, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 14—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>263. Sov[iet] military delegation arrived Riga yesterday ex Tallinn and
                            Moscow headed by <persName corresp="#p_IIS1">Isakov</persName>,
                            Assistant Commissar Navy, and General <persName corresp="#p_BIV1">Boldin</persName>, chief, <persName corresp="#p_KMI1">Kalinin</persName> Mil[itary] District.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WJC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>